3.60	Krishanti_Kumaraswamy	Krishanti Kumaraswamy	Krishanti Kumaraswamy (Tamil: ), also spelled Krishanthi Kumaraswamy, was a minority Tamil girl in Sri Lanka who was raped and murdered in 7 August 1996 by 6 Sri Lankan Army soldiers; the effort to bring her assailants to justice became a cause celebre as a part of the protest against atrocities committed by the Sri Lankan Army during the Sri Lanka civil war.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/50/Krishanthy.jpeg/100px-Krishanthy.jpeg
